  <!-- FAQs -->
  <section class="aw-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="aw-container">
      <div class="aw-section-header">
        <h2 class="aw-section-title">Apple Watch Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="aw-section-subtitle">Common questions about Apple Watch repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="aw-faq-list">
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does Apple Watch screen replacement take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Most Apple Watch screen replacements at our Winnipeg shop take 1–2 hours. We stock screens for all current Series, SE, and Ultra models so same-day repair is available for walk-ins.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Is my Apple Watch still water resistant after a screen repair?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">We reseal the display adhesive during every screen repair to restore the original water resistance rating. While we cannot guarantee the exact IP rating is fully restored, we take every precaution to maintain the seal quality.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does Apple Watch battery replacement cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Battery replacement costs vary by Apple Watch model and generation — older Series models are typically less expensive than newer ones. Contact our Winnipeg locations or use our online quote tool for an exact price on your specific model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Apple Watch Ultra and Ultra 2 in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair both Apple Watch Ultra and Ultra 2 at our Winnipeg St. Vital location. The larger 49mm case requires specialized tools that most general repair shops don't carry, but we have them in stock.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>How do I know if my Apple Watch battery needs replacing?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Signs of a worn battery include rapid drain during normal use, unexpected shutdowns at 20–30% charge, the watch not lasting through a full day, or the watch running warm. You can check battery maximum capacity in the Watch app on your iPhone under My Watch &gt; General &gt; Usage &gt; Battery Health.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix an Apple Watch that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Yes — a completely unresponsive Apple Watch is often caused by a fully depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a logic board fault. We run full diagnostics before recommending a repair so you know exactly what the issue is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Apple Watch SE in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all three generations of Apple Watch SE including the 1st Gen, 2nd Gen, and 3rd Gen models. Screen and battery replacements are the most common SE repairs and are typically completed same-day.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix Apple Watch water damage in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">In many cases yes — even water resistant Apple Watches can suffer damage from salt water, pool chemicals, or older degraded seals. We perform component-level cleaning and diagnostics to assess what can be recovered.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you offer a warranty on Apple Watch repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">Yes — screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on the part tier selected. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty. All other repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="aw-faq-item">
          <summary class="aw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do I need an appointment for Apple Watch repair in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="aw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="aw-faq-answer">No appointment is needed — both our St. Vital and Thompson locations accept walk-in Apple Watch repairs. Calling ahead is helpful to confirm we have your specific model's parts in stock, especially for newer Ultra 2 or Series 10 models.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

